32:00.152 --> 32:03.186
Shit. Are you all right, man?

32:07.927 --> 32:09.960
No lights.

32:09.962 --> 32:13.030
Look upon them rookie faces,
them panicking.

32:13.032 --> 32:16.466
I'd say, you don't know
any more than we do.

32:16.468 --> 32:19.102
[INMATES CHEERING]

32:19.104 --> 32:21.672
I know how to use this
fucking rifle, you black bitch.

32:24.076 --> 32:26.510
It's a shotgun, you fool.

32:26.512 --> 32:29.379
So go on, what's your plan?

32:30.983 --> 32:32.382
LENNON: What are you doing?

32:34.453 --> 32:37.087
[SIGHS] Look at
his face, that guard.

32:37.089 --> 32:38.722
[SNARLING]

32:39.458 --> 32:40.991
WOODHOUSE: Load up.

32:42.494 --> 32:44.027
Shoot to kill.

32:45.631 --> 32:48.498
We're gonna sweep
this block clean.

32:48.500 --> 32:52.102
I'm glad I get to
pull the trigger
on these fucking bitches.

32:52.104 --> 32:54.338
[SNARLING]

33:08.187 --> 33:10.087
I thought it was a prisoner.

33:10.089 --> 33:12.155
[SCREECHING]

33:12.157 --> 33:13.690
[SNARLING]

33:29.575 --> 33:31.408
Warden, are you there?

33:41.153 --> 33:44.021
[SNARLING]

33:48.227 --> 33:49.292
[SNARLING]

33:58.037 --> 33:59.102
[SNARLING]

33:59.104 --> 34:02.739
[GUARD GROANS]

34:15.087 --> 34:18.155
[SCREAMING]

34:25.563 --> 34:27.130
[SCREAMING]

34:38.077 --> 34:40.610
[GROWLING]

34:45.083 --> 34:47.083
Shoot to kill, right?

34:52.591 --> 34:56.326
[SCREAMING]

35:04.269 --> 35:05.836
BUTCHER: Get to the stairs.

35:14.746 --> 35:15.812
[INDISTINCT VOICE
ON WALKIE-TALKIE]

35:22.354 --> 35:23.787
STONE: For fuck's sake,
come on Lennon.

35:33.732 --> 35:35.499
Wait, there's more.

35:42.474 --> 35:43.573
[SHOTGUN COCKS]

35:43.575 --> 35:44.641
Lock it!

36:24.883 --> 36:27.517
[FLIES BUZZING]

36:27.519 --> 36:29.319
STONE: No one touch anything.

36:29.321 --> 36:32.289
FRANCINE: I ain't touching
any goddamn thing
ever again.

36:32.291 --> 36:35.358
How the fuck did you
get in C-block, you faggot?

36:35.360 --> 36:37.427
I'll take your
fucking face off, bitch.

36:37.896 --> 36:39.462
STONE: Shh!

36:39.464 --> 36:41.198
[GROWLING]

36:51.944 --> 36:53.677
Put the fucking
knife down, Butcher.

36:56.815 --> 36:59.783
There's enough death in here
without you turning
the place into a...

36:59.785 --> 37:02.719
Lennon, we can't let them
walk around in here
with our dicks in their hands.

37:02.721 --> 37:04.554
You don't have
no control in here.

37:06.792 --> 37:10.260
STRINGER: So,
who's in control then, huh?

37:10.662 --> 37:12.629
Who's in control?

37:12.631 --> 37:15.599
What? You and your addict girl
leading us now?

37:15.601 --> 37:17.785
We gotta keep moving.

37:17.786 --> 37:19.970
[SCOFFS] Trigger-happy
Captain Cuntface,
the voice of reason.

37:19.972 --> 37:22.339
-You need to relax.
-STRINGER: Relax?

37:22.341 --> 37:28.411
Relax? A pack of
misfit twats like you
won't make it four inches...

37:28.413 --> 37:30.347
-[SCREAMS]
-[SNARLING]

37:35.654 --> 37:36.920
[GUNSHOT]

37:36.922 --> 37:43.927
[GUNSHOTS AND SCREAMS]

37:49.268 --> 37:56.039
[COASTAL WEATHER FORECAST
ON RADIO]

38:17.429 --> 38:18.862
[BANG ON DOOR]

38:20.666 --> 38:21.998
What in the hell?

38:26.371 --> 38:28.438
[PANTING]

38:29.941 --> 38:33.510
You don't have no authority
around here anymore, governor.

38:33.512 --> 38:36.946
Officer Woodhouse,
shoot the Butcher, then Stone.

38:36.948 --> 38:38.748
We're all that's
left from out there.

38:38.749 --> 38:40.549
If you're gonna
get out of here alive,
you're gonna need us.

38:40.552 --> 38:43.353
And you need us
more than we need you.

38:43.355 --> 38:45.855
[SNARLING]

38:52.097 --> 38:53.496
Oh, Christ.

39:21.093 --> 39:22.892
These are our
medical files.

39:32.938 --> 39:36.072
Why do you have
my daughter's blood type?
And her details?

39:36.074 --> 39:37.974
Put them down.

39:37.976 --> 39:39.976
CROWE: You put your names
down for the tests.

39:40.846 --> 39:42.712
What do you expect?

39:42.714 --> 39:44.481
"Blood type: No Match."

39:44.483 --> 39:47.384
"Proceed." With what?
I didn't agree to anything.

39:47.386 --> 39:49.119
CROWE: Well, forget
about that now.

39:49.121 --> 39:51.554
Let's deal with
the present situation.

39:51.556 --> 39:53.723
Situation you started.

39:57.028 --> 39:58.461
[CLATTERING]

40:01.967 --> 40:03.867
There are more
survivors out there.

40:05.837 --> 40:08.171
Who's this?
Your girlfriend?

40:08.173 --> 40:11.141
Oi! Put that down.

40:14.579 --> 40:16.946
[PANTING AND GASPING]

40:19.618 --> 40:20.817
Put it down, junkie!

40:25.023 --> 40:27.991
Yo, yo, yo, come on.
Sit, now, sit.

40:33.732 --> 40:36.533
WOODHOUSE: Don't even think
about pouring that drink, nonce,

40:36.535 --> 40:40.103
or getting in this fucking
block will be your last
great escape.

40:40.105 --> 40:41.805
I'll make sure...

40:43.642 --> 40:45.108
STONE: Is the power down,
or was that a fuse?

40:46.978 --> 40:49.679
The surges blow the fuses.

40:49.681 --> 40:51.648
The box for this block
is in the laundry.

40:51.650 --> 40:53.683
STONE: That's next to
Dr. Brooks' office.

40:56.154 --> 40:57.654
We need a doctor up here.

41:01.726 --> 41:03.026
I'm all right, Stone.

41:04.596 --> 41:05.895
I'm still alive.

41:05.897 --> 41:08.031
But in the infirmary,
you saw how that spreads.

41:08.967 --> 41:10.567
I don't feel
any different.

41:10.936 --> 41:12.469
I don't have it.

41:17.075 --> 41:20.543
[DISTANT SCREAMING]

41:29.921 --> 41:34.190
[HEAVY BREATHING]

43:17.028 --> 43:18.094
[SNARLING]

43:22.100 --> 43:23.166
[SCREAMS]

43:34.980 --> 43:36.045
[SNARLING]

44:24.229 --> 44:26.329
[GLASS SHATTERS]

44:34.839 --> 44:36.439
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

44:39.344 --> 44:40.443
Stone?

44:40.445 --> 44:41.744
Shh!

44:44.783 --> 44:46.349
Stone!

44:50.021 --> 44:52.955
[SNARLING]

45:10.208 --> 45:11.874
Oh, my God!

45:19.851 --> 45:21.184
[SNARLING]

45:26.224 --> 45:27.974
Stone, what...

45:27.975 --> 45:29.725
Shh! Save it for
the warden's office
and keep quiet.

45:29.728 --> 45:31.060
[SNARLING]

45:31.062 --> 45:32.128
BROOKS: Shit!

45:43.274 --> 45:44.874
All full clips,

45:44.875 --> 45:46.475
bar one in the chamber.
They must have shot each other.

45:46.478 --> 45:49.312
What the hell
is happening?

45:49.314 --> 45:51.114
Come on,
you really don't know?

45:51.116 --> 45:54.417
I don't work in the labs.
Whatever this is, it's...

45:54.419 --> 45:55.752
Engineered.

45:55.754 --> 45:58.755
No shit! Take a gun.

45:58.757 --> 46:01.424
They're dead, Brooks. You're not
helping anyone by joining them.

46:05.163 --> 46:07.897
[SNARLING]

46:29.854 --> 46:31.988
You look like
you need a drink.

46:37.028 --> 46:38.427
Help yourself.

46:40.365 --> 46:42.165
Maybe they need to
fight and split.

46:48.039 --> 46:50.072
They'll likely
shoot each other?

46:50.074 --> 46:51.808
Ain't we supposed to be
helping them?

46:51.810 --> 46:53.810
Help them?

46:53.812 --> 46:57.180
What Warden means, rookie,
is we'll move faster
with less people.

46:57.182 --> 46:59.048
They're fucking dead
anyway.

47:00.952 --> 47:02.885
Get over there
and keep an eye on them.

47:06.925 --> 47:08.958
We're not moving anywhere.

47:08.960 --> 47:10.560
What's wrong with you?
You look like shit.

47:11.963 --> 47:13.262
It's just the heat.

47:16.267 --> 47:18.301
[GASPING]

47:19.304 --> 47:21.904
[GROANING]

47:28.012 --> 47:30.480
Tie her up.

47:30.481 --> 47:32.949
I'll show that fucking mute
my definition of cold turkey.

47:34.853 --> 47:37.520
[GRUNTING]

47:49.567 --> 47:51.500
These will
keep you going

47:53.438 --> 47:55.271
for a short while.

47:58.543 --> 48:01.277
Got a bit of an habit
of your own there, Doctor?

48:07.485 --> 48:11.087
[SNARLING ECHOING
IN THE DISTANCE]

48:29.240 --> 48:31.540
STONE: The new prisoner
was brought back in
from the island.

48:31.542 --> 48:33.109
He tried to escape.

48:33.111 --> 48:37.079
Which means, it could be worse
out there than it is in here.

48:38.082 --> 48:40.383
My sister's out there.

48:40.385 --> 48:45.021
It seems to spread
through blood
and possibly saliva.

48:45.023 --> 48:47.623
It means any of you
could be infected
and we won't even know.

48:49.227 --> 48:50.526
STONE: We have to
find a way out.

48:55.333 --> 48:56.482
They seem to hate light.

48:56.483 --> 48:57.632
We wait until dawn.
Then we can walk out of here.

48:58.236 --> 48:59.635
Walk out?

48:59.637 --> 49:02.204
There's no way
off the island.

49:03.174 --> 49:05.708
Where do you think
you'll walk to?

49:15.019 --> 49:16.419
Looks like your girl
Butcher over there

49:16.421 --> 49:18.220
is too good
for the rest of us.

49:19.624 --> 49:21.390
Warden don't include
a new guard,

49:21.392 --> 49:24.026
but a bitch who
cut up 20 people?

49:24.028 --> 49:26.362
Yeah, but 20 members
of the National Front.

49:26.364 --> 49:28.230
So things aren't
so black and white, are they?

49:28.232 --> 49:30.366
You're gonna need
to choose a side.

49:30.368 --> 49:33.035
Ain't gonna be
a hard choice, is it?

49:33.037 --> 49:35.004
I'm locking up,
not locked up.

49:35.640 --> 49:37.573
Well, you're locked up now.

49:37.575 --> 49:40.076
You little bitch.

49:40.078 --> 49:41.978
You wanna get off
this island alive?

49:41.980 --> 49:43.646
That little committee
over there

49:43.647 --> 49:45.313
are the only things
standing between us
and getting out.

49:45.316 --> 49:47.450
And a hundred
diseased inmates.

49:47.452 --> 49:49.752
And that there
is our bait.

49:49.754 --> 49:51.253
You don't owe'em shit.

49:52.023 --> 49:53.522
They're gonna kill you, too.

49:55.660 --> 49:57.360
What are you talking about?

49:57.362 --> 49:59.695
You ain't getting anywhere
in this dump without me.

49:59.697 --> 50:02.031
How did you get into
the women's block anyway?

50:02.033 --> 50:04.300
I was gonna ask you
the same thing, sweetheart.

50:04.302 --> 50:08.738
Once a week, people come
from the mainland with supplies.

50:08.740 --> 50:13.142
Without communications,
that won't be for
another five days.

50:13.144 --> 50:15.511
BUTCHER: How does it feel
to be trapped?

50:15.513 --> 50:20.783
May I remind you exactly why
you're trapped here?

50:20.785 --> 50:24.720
I'm guessing you've killed
more people than I ever could.

50:24.722 --> 50:27.623
So don't lecture me
about breaking the law, bitch.

50:27.625 --> 50:29.725
[GASPING]

50:33.564 --> 50:35.464
Wait. Wait, wait, wait.

50:36.034 --> 50:37.266
He's infected!

50:37.268 --> 50:38.434
No!

50:38.436 --> 50:40.436
Fuck that.
Do him now.

50:40.438 --> 50:43.773
Help me.
[GASPING]

50:43.775 --> 50:45.341
Brooks, there's got to be
something you can do.

50:45.343 --> 50:47.309
-Stone, I've told you.
-Bullshit!

50:49.447 --> 50:50.546
Oh, no.

50:51.616 --> 50:53.215
He saved my life.

50:58.423 --> 51:00.156
Help him, or I swear!

51:12.503 --> 51:13.736
What's that?

51:17.341 --> 51:18.674
LENNON: Saint Leonard,

51:19.610 --> 51:22.078
patron saint of prisoners.

51:22.080 --> 51:24.480
This island's named after him.

51:26.117 --> 51:28.451
You just gotta
have faith, Stone.

51:30.621 --> 51:33.355
Faith hasn't done me
many favors.

51:33.357 --> 51:35.791
You don't believe in heaven?

51:35.793 --> 51:38.661
If there is one, you and Brooks
are the only ones getting in.

51:40.131 --> 51:42.131
Probably due to naivety
more than anything else.

51:42.133 --> 51:44.233
[GASPING DEEPLY]

51:52.343 --> 51:53.876
Our Father,

51:54.512 --> 51:56.712
who art in heaven,

51:56.714 --> 51:58.747
hallowed be thy name.

52:01.352 --> 52:03.686
<i> The beach.</i>

52:05.256 --> 52:07.623
The beach.

52:09.327 --> 52:12.361
<i> It is beautiful.</i>

52:15.666 --> 52:17.433
[SCREAMS]

52:17.435 --> 52:19.135
Brooks, do something!

52:22.140 --> 52:23.606
Fuck!

52:23.608 --> 52:25.207
[SCREAMING]

52:25.209 --> 52:27.610
[GRUNTING]

52:31.916 --> 52:34.517
[SCREAMING]

52:36.287 --> 52:37.353
Quick!

52:38.589 --> 52:40.189
I can't help him.

52:40.558 --> 52:44.293
[SCREAMING]

52:48.833 --> 52:51.567
[GASPING]

52:55.806 --> 52:56.872
Please.

53:00.178 --> 53:01.443
Please.

53:06.617 --> 53:08.584
[SCREAMING]

53:09.921 --> 53:11.687
[SOBBING]

53:47.225 --> 53:49.959
[INMATES SCREAMING]

53:56.901 --> 53:59.702
[METAL CLANGING]

54:01.939 --> 54:04.406
[POUNDING ON DOOR]

54:07.745 --> 54:10.913
BROOKS: That's the main gate.
More survivors.

54:10.915 --> 54:12.715
They're probably fucking
riddled with it out there.

54:12.717 --> 54:14.450
We can't just
leave them out there.

54:14.452 --> 54:15.551
Yes, we fucking can.

54:15.553 --> 54:18.254
It's a fucking act.
Just leave them.

54:18.256 --> 54:20.623
My baby girl is out there.

54:21.826 --> 54:22.992
[SNIFFLES]

54:27.732 --> 54:31.400
You're just going to delay
my search with that ankle,
army girl.

54:31.402 --> 54:32.768
It takes two
to open those gates.

54:32.770 --> 54:34.436
So what do you
have out there, Stone?

54:35.406 --> 54:36.572
Brooks, you stay here.

54:36.574 --> 54:38.574
The people who need help
are out there.

54:38.576 --> 54:40.409
Oh, so you're a hero now?

54:42.013 --> 54:43.912
They'll kill you
the minute you go out there.

54:43.914 --> 54:45.614
My sister's out there.

54:45.616 --> 54:47.016
What's the quickest
way outside?

54:47.018 --> 54:48.684
CROWE: Through
the main cell block.

55:40.938 --> 55:44.907
Oh, dear Mary,
mother of Jesus.

55:49.080 --> 55:51.547
-Oh, the smell.
-Shh.

55:52.817 --> 55:55.517
Look, the lights
are still trying
to come on.

55:55.519 --> 55:58.554
Generators aren't topped up.
They won't last long.

55:59.090 --> 56:00.422
STONE: Where are they?

56:00.424 --> 56:01.924
Outside the prison walls.

56:03.394 --> 56:04.960
Any other source of power
in this place?

56:06.030 --> 56:08.497
Only the generators
for the electric chairs.

56:08.499 --> 56:10.432
They stay fully-charged.

56:10.434 --> 56:13.902
Yeah, you really have
your priorities right, eh?

56:44.402 --> 56:46.769
[CLAMORING IN THE DISTANCE]

56:48.706 --> 56:51.640
[POUNDING ON DOOR]

57:00.618 --> 57:03.419
[CLAMORING CONTINUES]

57:10.127 --> 57:12.761
We can't see what we're
dealing with from here.

57:12.763 --> 57:15.864
-I'm finding my sister.
-My baby girl, too.

57:28.979 --> 57:31.780
[CLAMORING CONTINUES]

57:37.488 --> 57:38.787
[CROWE EXHALES DEEPLY]

57:38.789 --> 57:40.189
[SNIFFLES]

57:50.000 --> 57:51.967
Be sure to kill anything
that isn't human.

57:53.204 --> 57:55.737
-They're all human.
-I'm serious.

58:16.260 --> 58:19.895
-[CLAMORING INTENSIFIES]
-[GUNSHOTS]

58:21.198 --> 58:23.832
[GUNSHOTS IN THE DISTANCE]

58:57.668 --> 58:59.601
[ALL BREATHING HEAVILY]

59:00.804 --> 59:02.037
You left the gates open.

59:02.039 --> 59:05.908
[SOBBING] No.
Oh, my baby.

59:05.910 --> 59:09.645
My little baby.
Jesus, what have I done?

59:11.949 --> 59:13.181
[LOUD THUD ON DOOR]

59:18.155 --> 59:19.821
Daylight's not the problem.

59:26.096 --> 59:28.664
Okay. All right,
look at me.

59:29.166 --> 59:30.933
Okay.

59:35.673 --> 59:38.640
-Is she okay?
-I think she's in shock.

59:38.642 --> 59:40.842
-[SCREECHING]
-[GROWLING]

01:00:03.233 --> 01:00:04.700
[DOOR OPENS]

01:00:12.977 --> 01:00:15.811
Girl, did you see
my sister out there?

01:00:15.813 --> 01:00:20.215
Elizabeth, my age,
short, grey hair.

01:00:20.217 --> 01:00:21.883
Could people have
splintered off in the panic?

01:00:21.885 --> 01:00:24.303
-I don't know.
-Hey, don't worry.

01:00:24.304 --> 01:00:26.722
We're gonna get out of here
as soon as we can make a call
to the mainland.

01:00:27.324 --> 01:00:28.857
We'll see.

01:00:38.168 --> 01:00:40.969
I wasn't expecting
visitors today.

01:00:42.406 --> 01:00:47.776
You know,
I knew a little girl
just like you once.

01:00:47.778 --> 01:00:50.178
Hey, man,
touch her again,

01:00:50.180 --> 01:00:52.014
and you're gonna feel
real pain.

01:00:57.388 --> 01:00:59.755
We need to find somewhere
more secure.

01:01:00.791 --> 01:01:02.991
It's not exactly
safe in here.

01:01:02.993 --> 01:01:04.693
Isolation.

01:01:04.695 --> 01:01:05.861
It's close,
and pretty tight
down there,

01:01:05.863 --> 01:01:07.396
if we get power
back to that block.

01:01:07.398 --> 01:01:09.965
It's got real
quiet outside.

01:01:09.967 --> 01:01:11.933
Maybe it's over.

01:01:11.935 --> 01:01:14.102
Just stick close together.

01:01:41.031 --> 01:01:42.731
STONE: The Butcher was right.

01:01:43.734 --> 01:01:45.400
BROOKS: About what?

01:01:45.402 --> 01:01:47.002
STONE: It's gone quiet.

01:01:49.206 --> 01:01:51.173
BROOKS: Maybe it's over.

01:01:51.175 --> 01:01:54.910
I mean, how long
could something survive
in that state?

01:03:01.211 --> 01:03:04.546
CHLOE: "If I shall die
before I wake,

01:03:04.548 --> 01:03:06.948
"I pray the Lord
my soul to take.

01:03:12.956 --> 01:03:15.857
"And should I live
for other days,

01:03:15.859 --> 01:03:18.326
"I pray that God
will guide my ways."

01:03:35.112 --> 01:03:37.379
BROOKS: Trying to remember
who you are, Stone?

01:03:39.516 --> 01:03:42.250
Are you planning to die
a martyr, Dr. Brooks?

01:03:44.021 --> 01:03:46.354
I was hoping
not to die at all.

01:03:47.825 --> 01:03:49.124
You?

01:03:49.860 --> 01:03:51.860
It makes no difference.

01:03:51.862 --> 01:03:54.462
They get me out there
or they put me
on the chair in here.

01:04:03.574 --> 01:04:06.374
How do you resign
yourself to death?

01:04:12.916 --> 01:04:15.517
I, err... [SCOFFS]

01:04:17.621 --> 01:04:20.188
Run out of words
of wisdom?

01:04:23.160 --> 01:04:25.026
I knew the Senator's family.

01:04:30.601 --> 01:04:34.035
I think that everyone,
for whatever reason,

01:04:34.037 --> 01:04:35.971
is in here because of him.

01:04:39.076 --> 01:04:42.077
I've profiled murderers
for nine years.

01:04:42.079 --> 01:04:43.378
You didn't do it.

01:04:44.414 --> 01:04:47.082
He did, didn't he?

